Vane RPS Alignment MATLAB Package
==================================

Files
-----
1. vane_rps_alignment.m
   Main function. Keep it on the MATLAB path.

2. example_vane_alignment.m
   Template showing required inputs and outputs.

Recommended input files
-----------------------
- nominal_vane.stl
- deform_springback_surface.stl
- cad_8_corners.csv
- scan_8_corners.csv
- wenzel_nominal_targets.csv

Each CSV has X,Y,Z columns with no text header unless you modify readmatrix.

How normals are obtained
------------------------
XYZ coordinates alone are insufficient to define a surface normal.

Preferred order:
1. Ask WENZEL to export nominal point direction vectors (I,J,K or Nx,Ny,Nz).
2. Otherwise export the nominal CAD to a fine STL.
3. The main function finds the closest CAD triangle for each WENZEL target and
   averages nearby, similarly oriented triangle normals.

For a target on a sharp edge or fillet, the normal is ambiguous and will depend
on tessellation and averaging. Move the target into the interior of the intended
datum surface whenever possible.

Classic 3-2-1 RPS
-----------------
For A1,A2,A3,B1,B2,C1, use the actual CAD surface normal at every point.
Do not manually force A normals to be exactly identical unless that matches the
WENZEL point definitions.

The function reports the rank of the RPS Jacobian. It must be 6 for a fully
constrained rigid alignment. A very high condition number indicates weak
geometry or poor target spacing.

STL quality
-----------
Use a fine enough CAD STL that the local triangle normal represents the exact
CAD surface. Curved shoulders need finer tessellation than flat datum faces.

Projection
----------
After 8-corner coarse alignment, each nominal CAD target is ray-cast in both
normal directions onto the distorted mesh. The nearest hit is used.

Keep maxProjectionDistance only slightly larger than the expected mismatch.
A large value can hit the opposite side of a thin vane.

If WENZEL exports the actual measured datum point XYZ values in the original scan
coordinate system, provide:
    cfg.measuredDatumPointsScan = readmatrix("measured_points.csv");
Then mesh projection is bypassed.
